      <br> <br>
      <button type="button" class="btn btn-success" data-bs-toggle="modal" data-bs-target="#exampleModal">
      Learn More: My IoT Device [Master's Thesis Project]
      </button>
      <div class="modal fade" id="exampleModal" tabindex="-1" aria-labelledby="exampleModalLabel" aria-hidden="true">
         <div class="modal-dialog modal-dialog-centered">
            <div class="modal-content">
               <div class="modal-header">
                  <h1 class="modal-title fs-5" id="exampleModalLabel">Device Features</h1>
                  <button type="button" class="btn-close" data-bs-dismiss="modal" aria-label="Close"></button>
               </div>
               <div class="modal-body" style="text-align: left;">
                  I built an IoT device (Portable Monitoring Unit 4.0) to continually monitor environmental parameters in commercial poultry facilities and transmit near real-time data reports to the cloud, replacing the tedious on-site data retrieval.
                  <br> <br>
                  <ul class="checklist">
                     <li>Near real-time data streaming</li>
                     <li>Triple redundant data persistence mechanism</li>
                     <li>System health reporting with a heartbeat</li>
                     <li>Critical events reporting</li>
                     <li>Many more features</li>
                  </ul>
               </div>
               <div class="modal-footer">
                  <button type="button" class="btn btn-secondary" data-bs-dismiss="modal">Close</button>
               </div>
            </div>
         </div>
      </div>
